{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.41",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 41,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 41",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 41 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:1",
      "text": "“Can you draw out Leviathan with a fish hook, or press down his tongue with a cord?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:2",
      "text": "Can you put a rope into his nose, or pierce his jaw through with a hook?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:3",
      "text": "Will he make many petitions to you, or will he speak soft words to you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:4",
      "text": "Will he make a covenant with you, that you should take him for a servant forever?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:5",
      "text": "Will you play with him as with a bird? Or will you bind him for your girls?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:6",
      "text": "Will traders barter for him? Will they part him among the merchants?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:7",
      "text": "Can you fill his skin with barbed irons, or his head with fish spears?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:8",
      "text": "Lay your hand on him. Remember the battle, and do so no more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:9",
      "text": "Behold, the hope of him is in vain. Won’t one be cast down even at the sight of him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:10",
      "text": "None is so fierce that he dare stir him up. Who then is he who can stand before me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:11",
      "text": "Who has first given to me, that I should repay him? Everything under the heavens is mine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:12",
      "text": "“I will not keep silence concerning his limbs, nor his mighty strength, nor his goodly frame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:13",
      "text": "Who can strip off his outer garment? Who will come within his jaws?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:14",
      "text": "Who can open the doors of his face? Around his teeth is terror.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:15",
      "text": "Strong scales are his pride, shut up together with a close seal.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:16",
      "text": "One is so near to another, that no air can come between them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:17",
      "text": "They are joined to one another. They stick together, so that they can’t be pulled apart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:18",
      "text": "His sneezing flashes out light. His eyes are like the eyelids of the morning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:19",
      "text": "Out of his mouth go burning torches. Sparks of fire leap out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:20",
      "text": "Out of his nostrils a smoke goes, as of a boiling pot over a fire of reeds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:21",
      "text": "His breath kindles coals. A flame goes out of his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:22",
      "text": "There is strength in his neck. Terror dances before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:23",
      "text": "The flakes of his flesh are joined together. They are firm on him. They can’t be moved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:24",
      "text": "His heart is as firm as a stone, yes, firm as the lower millstone.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:25",
      "text": "When he raises himself up, the mighty are afraid. They retreat before his thrashing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:26",
      "text": "If one attacks him with the sword, it can’t prevail; nor the spear, the dart, nor the pointed shaft.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:27",
      "text": "He counts iron as straw, and bronze as rotten wood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:28",
      "text": "The arrow can’t make him flee. Sling stones are like chaff to him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:29",
      "text": "Clubs are counted as stubble. He laughs at the rushing of the javelin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:30",
      "text": "His undersides are like sharp potsherds, leaving a trail in the mud like a threshing sledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:31",
      "text": "He makes the deep to boil like a pot. He makes the sea like a pot of ointment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:32",
      "text": "He makes a path shine after him. One would think the deep had white hair.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:33",
      "text": "On earth there is not his equal, that is made without fear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.41.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 41,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 41:34",
      "text": "He sees everything that is high. He is king over all the sons of pride.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
